"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"67a7eb4ab4d670618766616cef50f4f17eec9b582363cbac2b337580062992b5","event_uuid":"73ba57ad-2136-49b9-9494-b83c7c4fa51c","position":{"commit_sha":"20efd985f7bc3981e9165adbfaeef03b34150a51","position":"1784446198596527572-73ba57ad-2136-49b9-9494-b83c7c4fa51c"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416754695235001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"5d94fbb9-472a-4d14-8350-b8273c5fbfc2","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a"}],"description":"## What\nRead-only derivations over git history + the working tree for the code-health metrics that are durably git-derivable **under the current module-size mechanism**: module-size distribution against the hard cap, cap-change events, short-term churn, and the refactor-to-addition ratio.\n\n## Current mechanism (the plan is grounded in this, not the deleted ratchet)\nThe old per-file ceilings ratchet is **gone**: `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` and `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` were deleted (epic 716f). Module size is now a **single, flat, admin-locked hard cap** in `.github/module-size-limit.txt` (currently `800`). So the metrics derive from (a) scanning `src/rebar/**/*.py` line counts against that single-sourced cap, and (b) `git log`. There is **no** \"allowlisted-module count\", \"total ceiling LOC\", or \"new vs raised ceilings\" to read.\n\n## The raw metric functions (multi-arg; the implementation)\nIn `src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py`, all read-only and deterministic:\n- `module_size_distribution(repo_root, ref=\"HEAD\") -> dict` → `{\"count\": <n .py modules>, \"near_cap_count\": <within 10% of the cap>, \"over_cap_count\": <exceeding the cap>, \"max_loc\": <largest module LOC>}`. The cap is read from `.github/module-size-limit.txt` (single-sourced, never hardcoded). Scans `src/rebar/**/*.py` at the ref.\n- `cap_change_events(repo_root, since, until) -> list[dict]` → a list (possibly empty) of `{\"commit\", \"old_limit\", \"new_limit\"}` dicts from `git log` over `.github/module-size-limit.txt` in range. **Return type is always a `list[dict]`** — `[]` for a range with no cap change (a real \"no events\" result, distinct from the Unavailable path).\n- `churn(repo_root, since, until) -> dict` → `{\"insertions\": <int>, \"deletions\": <int>}` summed from `git log --numstat` over the range.\n- `refactor_to_addition_ratio(repo_root, since, until) -> float | None` → deletions/insertions from numstat. Returns **`None`** when total insertions over the range is `0` (no additions to divide by — no data / avoids ZeroDivisionError); a populated range with real deletions of 0 returns `0.0`.\n\n## Registration into the c085 registry (the compute-adapter contract)\nc085's `MetricSpec.compute` is a **`Callable[[context], value | None]`** invoked by `evaluate()` as `spec.compute(context)` (registry.py:103-111). The raw functions above are multi-arg, so each `MetricSpec.compute` is a **single-arg adapter** that pulls the range from the context and calls the raw function, e.g. `compute=lambda ctx: churn(ctx.repo_root, ctx.since, ctx.until)`. The context is the small object the `rebar metrics` command (9a5a) passes to every compute, carrying `repo_root`, `since`, `until` (a metric that ignores the range, like `module_size_distribution`, simply reads `ctx.repo_root`). Each of the four `MetricSpec` entries sets: `lens=\"code_health\"`, `source=\"git\"`, `confidence=\"high\"`, `accruing_since=\"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"` (git history predates the metrics work, so these are available immediately — not `unavailable`), and the wrapping `compute`. A compute that finds no data in range returns `None` so `evaluate()` reports `Unavailable`.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py` — new: the four functions above + their four `MetricSpec` registrations appended to `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`'s `REGISTRY` (unique ids `module_size_distribution`, `cap_change_events`, `churn`, `refactor_to_addition_ratio`).\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nEverything is deterministic and read-only. Distribution scans the tree at a ref against the single-sourced cap (no deleted files parsed); churn/refactor come from `git log --numstat`; cap changes from the limit file's history. Registered into the c085 registry via context-adapter computes. `source=\"git\"`, `confidence=\"high\"` (authoritative). Nothing is written.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp git repo): a fixture tree with modules of known sizes yields the expected `module_size_distribution` (count/max_loc/over_cap_count against a fixture cap file); a `git log --numstat` fixture yields the expected `churn` totals and `refactor_to_addition_ratio`; a commit changing `.github/module-size-limit.txt` is surfaced by `cap_change_events`; an all-additions range yields a valid ratio while a zero-insertions range yields `None`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py` passes against a temp git repo: `module_size_distribution` over a fixture tree returns `max_loc` equal to the largest fixture module's line count, `count` equal to the number of `.py` modules, and `over_cap_count` equal to the number exceeding the fixture cap (exact-value asserts on all three).\n- [ ] `churn` over a two-commit numstat fixture returns the exact summed `{\"insertions\", \"deletions\"}`; `refactor_to_addition_ratio` over the same fixture returns the exact deletions/insertions ratio, and returns `None` when total insertions is 0 (asserted).\n- [ ] `cap_change_events` over a commit changing `.github/module-size-limit.txt` returns a `list[dict]` containing `{\"old_limit\",\"new_limit\"}` with the old and new values; a range with no such commit returns `[]` (both asserted — the return type is a list in both cases).\n- [ ] each of the four metric ids (`module_size_distribution`, `cap_change_events`, `churn`, `refactor_to_addition_ratio`) is present in `REGISTRY` with `lens=\"code_health\"`, `source=\"git\"`, `confidence=\"high\"` — asserted by iterating `REGISTRY` and checking `.id`/`.lens`/`.source` (so the assertion fails if a metric is unregistered or mislabeled, not merely that `is_authoritative(\"git\")` is trivially True).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py","reason":"git-derivation readers"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","c085-6d11-d68d-422a"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"c6f75617-2328-40ec-a319-a83b69675fa2","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"7931-e644-30de-4023","ticket_type":"task","title":"Git-derivation readers (code-health metrics from git history)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["22b1b826-c3da-4bd1-8a92-edc1dd7ec884","b3f73abc-856c-49f4-9394-b8feb0aebd88","5d94fbb9-472a-4d14-8350-b8273c5fbfc2","ea7bb22b-b803-48ec-b306-7eead3999987","40cb5777-891a-48c6-ae73-6ad72a2af06e","785b65dc-3e96-4d78-9821-94b710741504","022cb4c3-5dd8-4de1-b366-c33dadae7a50","52270a16-b321-48ec-9d8d-3ad472499dec","d91ef6f6-6f0d-49bb-9b53-299efb1ae691","4d8207e8-97ba-4734-ba02-f953b04b4